<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-02-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Russell</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-02-19"><hi rend="italic">February 19,
                                    1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Root informs Mr. Russell that the French Government has consented to
                            allow our consuls in France to take charge of the papers and archives of
                            Venezuela, without performing consular functions.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>